post_text:
🚕 Parent drop-off in the A.M.: No earlier than 8:30 a.m. and no later than 8:50 a.m. No student may be dropped off prior to 8:30 a.m.

🚗 Parent pick-up in the P.M.: Students will be escorted to their vehicle, parents will sign their child out at their vehicle through the vehicle window and must show ID to the staff member. Pre-K and kindergarten pick-up is from 3:00 p.m.-3:05 p.m. Grades one through six pick-up is between 3:10 p.m.-3:20 p.m.

🚸 Please be patient and anticipate delays, especially in the beginning of the year. Safety is our number one priority.

Kayla Hart, Oriskany Class of 2004, has donated backpacks to the Oriskany School District. Ms. Hart, who works for AD Sutton & Sons in New York City, is the Social Media Coordinator for Bags in Bulk. Two large boxes arrived containing 68 backpacks of various styles and colors.

If you are in need of backpacks for your children, feel free to stop by the elementary school. They will be available in the foyer on a first come first serve basis. Oriskany Central School is very appreciative of Ms. Hart, AD Sutton & Sons and Bags in Bulk for thinking about our students. 🎒 #OriskanyProud

Oriskany Central School District added 67 new photos.
July 22 at 1:34 PM ·

On July 19, Oriskany CSD seniors participated in a socially distant graduation on the Bernie Block football field at the elementary school. Due to the Governor’s mandates surrounding COVID-19, each senior was allowed to bring two guests, as participants and attendees socially distanced through a ceremony that included the traditional speeches from the valedictorian, Kara Daskiewich and salutatorian, Angelina Hays, as well as the singing of both the Oriskany Alma Mater and the National Anthem.

Friends and family members who were not able to attend were able to see the event live streamed on the district website.

Congratulations to the Class of 2020! #OriskanyProud

Oneida-Herkimer-Madison BOCES
May 28 at 9:01 AM ·

📅REMINDER that local school budget votes and Board of Education elections are coming up on Tuesday, June 9! 📅

All NYS school budget votes and BOE elections are being held via absentee ballot this year. Absentee ballots with postage-paid return envelopes are being mailed to each “qualified voter.” A qualified voter is a U.S. citizen, 18 years of age or older, a resident of the District for at least 30 days prior to the vote, and not disqualified by any reason set forth by NYS Election Laws.

Completed absentee ballots must be received by the school district in which you reside no later than 5:00 p.m. on the date of the election, Tuesday, June 9, 2020.

Please refer to your school district’s budget notice, budget newsletter and website for detailed information on the 2020-21 proposed budget and BOE candidates.

March 30 at 6:05 AM · Oriskany, NY ·

Good morning from the Oneida County Sheriff’s Office. We visited the Oriskany Central School District for today’s Pledge of Allegiance. We will be continue to visit local schools and public places with flags proudly displayed during our social isolation period.

Recited by Undersheriff Joseph Lisi

I pledge Allegiance to the flag
of the United States of America
and to the Republic for which it stands,
one nation under God, indivisible,
with Liberty and Justice for all.

Child care placement is available to personnel who provide essential services, supplies, or support during this unprecedented time. For a full list of personnel who may qualify, please visit our website at www.oriskanycsd.org.

Essential personnel can call the Oneida-Herkimer-Madison Child Care Resource Center at 315-223-7850 extension 222 or email earlycareandlearning@cornell.edu for information on childcare
placement.

The Child Care Resource Center will continue to evaluate and adjust plans as necessary to best meet the childcare needs of essential personnel.

Thank you to all essential personnel who continue to protect and support our community.

Please be safe, and whenever possible, stay at home.

Julia Harrison Stapleton is with Mel Rivera and 5 others.
March 21 at 8:30 PM ·

10 years old & Jayden is sewing face masks to donate to those in need (with a little guidance from mom) . ❤️ He learned how to do this TODAY!! Couldn’t be more proud of him!

*If anyone has any spare fabric they would like to donate to help or 1/4” elastic band let us know !! We will be making them all week !*

Edited to add, these are FREE as long as we have enough supplies! Just pay shipping or if you have to work close by we can arrange a safe pick up 🙂 Keep in mind, these are NOT medical grade masks.

Oriskany Central School District added 11 new photos — at N A Walbran Elementary School.
January 29 at 12:57 PM · Oriskany, NY ·

On Jan. 24, Oriskany Elementary students and staff came together for a BEE Kind assembly.

The assembly included a lesson from Principal Hinderling on how to be kind, the reading of a story about kindness as well as the honoring of a student who is a cancer survivor.

Following the assembly, students participated in a variety of math related activities; including St. Jude’s Math-A-Thon.

Collectively, N.A. Walbran was able to donate almost $600 to St. Jude’s! #OriskanyProud
